<br>
The real problem here is that guilds go to the planes for 3 different reasons, yet we only have 2 ways to handle who gets the mobs.<br>
<br>
RandomSmallGuild01 goes to get armor and weapons for it's members. RandomUberGuild goes to kill the gods and sometimes demis for epics. A bunch of others could care less about the armor and aren't really strong enough to do the gods, but still need demis for epics. We've taken care of the gods, but the demis are still a problem.<br>
<br>
I don't think giving a guild that is gonna let the armor and such rot more cal IDs is going to really solve anything. Each raid will still have basically a 1 in 3 chance of having any demis up. Someone could go to Fear 20 times in 1 month and not see a demi, if their luck was bad enough.<br>
<br>
